Our Stax Cares program is how Suneera and I give back to our community in time and dollars donated.

Stax Cares has three core principles:

1️⃣ Women in Business
2️⃣ Youth in Stem
3️⃣ Radical Acceptance

Last year, we pledged to give $1M over the next three years, and we’ve already surpassed our 2022 goal! 🙏🏽

For the kids this year, we partnered with the Arnold Palmer Hospital to deliver Christmas presents to terminally ill patients and kids with tough cases.

Our amazing Stax Pack dropped off over 1,000 toys this year! 🎅 🤶 🧸 

We’ve been doing this every year since we started our company, and someone recently asked me, “What’s the feeling you get from doing all that?”

I honestly feel privileged to be able to do this.

It may sound selfish to say, but I get so much more joy than any kid opening a present.

It also reminds me of why we do this: to leave a legacy of positive impact and change.

And hopefully, to inspire others to do the same. 💜 🎄

BDHP 🥂🔥➡️ The Best Damn Holiday Party happened last week👏🏽

Our team knows how important traditions are to me.

@salrehmetullah and I moved around a lot as kids, so when our family finally settled in Orlando, I was determined to make it feel like home by establishing traditions. And we infused that same spirit into our company.

At @staxpayments, one of our most beloved traditions is The Best Damn Holiday Party (yes, that’s what it’s called) we hold annually. 

We even have traditions WITHIN traditions.

During The Best Damn Holiday Party, we give out “X-Factor” awards, peer-nominated and leadership-endorsed recognition of outstanding team members from every department. 

2022 was everything that it was because of our people. One of the hardest -yet best- years so far and this was the celebration of all our hard work. 

PLUS we didn’t only celebrate the end of an awesome year of smashing goals but also 9 years in business!! So excited for our 10th this next year.

After such an amazing year in business, it’s wonderful to celebrate all the people who helped us achieve it. And *that’s* my most favorite tradition of all.

Merry Everything! 

I decided to take a mini social break to unwind over the holidays and keep some family time private this year. 

We closed out our recording breaking Stax year, the podcast season that took us to top 25, and I just finished enrolling our 2023 cohort of @ceoschool Ceo’s for our next class. I am exhausted, and exhilarated all at the same time.

Stax @staxpayments 💜 | Part 1/3 of my 2022 breakdown series 

Wow... where to begin 🤯

This year was CRAZY for Stax to say the least. We, as a team, accomplished things that young Sal and Sunny wouldn’t even dream of. @salrehmetullah

Our year started strong with us announcing that we achieved unicorn status which was mythical. Less than 2% of female founders ever break 1M in revenue and less than 3% ever even get a shot at raising venture capital. So our year started by defying the odds. 

A minority-led Fintech became Florida's first unicorn, and we even got an entire day named after us! March 8th will forever be a day to remember 💜💜

Things only went up from there and we celebrated incredible moments like winning @incmagazine "Best Place to Work" and making @usnews World Reports annual list as The Best Credit Card Processor! 👏🏽 + INC even did a profile on my dad and how he influenced our journey!

Amongst other - not less amazing- things (like making NASDAQ in TIME SQUARE 🤯) , we experienced one of the highlights of my 2022 with a full circle moment at @money20_20. Nine years ago, my cofounders and I pooled our money for one badge for @jaqueskfu while Sal and I drummed up business on the sidelines. This year, the three of us went, not just as attendees, but, we also graced the MAIN stage!! 😍 AND made other appearances at conferences like EY and Hubspot ⚡️

One of my favorite days EVER? ➡️ we committed to 1M in helping our community with our time and dollars - one of the big events was @comeoutwithpride Orlando where we celebrated our team and being our most authentic selves ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜 

To top it all off, we celebrated an amazing year in business with all the people who helped us achieve it at the BDHP. 🥂 

I'm happy to say this year completely topped my vision board (and if you know me you know it was already ambitious enough), and I couldn’t be more excited for what's to come. 

Huge shoutout to my #staxpack @staxpayments. I could never accomplish all these things without you. You rock 🖤

PS: let this be your reminder that, if I can do it, so can you. 😉

CEO School @ceoschool 💗💚 | Part 2/3 of my 2022 breakdown series 

You ask how I manage it all- when you make what you love your job, you find a way.

This year was nothing shy of amazing from scaling the podcast , leveling up production, throwing 3 retreats, building out a course, building out our community for 6 figure + entrepreneurs inside The Boardroom and of course our brand new APP 🤯

My dad would’ve been 60 today and I still can’t believe it’s been 2.5 years since the last time I hugged him.

For those that don’t know:

My father was my biggest role model. Not just because I was daddy’s girl, but also because he was the greatest businessman and work-life integrator. Ever. 

He left Pakistan as a young kid to build his future in America where he met my mother. They went on to build their mini empire which allowed for my brother and I to learn every business lesson from him and to build our dreams together as a family - 

His day to day was my favorite - he woke up at the crack of dawn every morning, happy and singing, and went to the mosque right after. Gratitude for his life and the pursuit of peace in prayer were engraved in him. 

Then he would open the business. Whatever business. He was always the first one there. 

He would then spend the rest of his hours with my girls at the park or in his beautiful yard filled with fruits and vegetables. 

I hope to be half as consistent as my father one day. 

Missing you dad , everyday . Your legacy lives on with me and salman and your grand kids . 🤍

IS WHAT YOU'RE DOING TODAY MOVING YOU CLOSER TO YOUR DREAM LIFE? 

if yes, keep scrolling ✔️
if not, keep reading...

yes, it's scary. whatever you want: your big, hairy, ambitious goals. it's scary to think you might fail. 

you might even be scared of the person you need to embody when you actually achieve those goals... 

but fear will keep you stagnant... for years. 

I believe every woman should have it all -- success on her terms. But I also know it's not easy to get there. 

Here's what you need to do: 

⚡️ Scared? We all are. Do it anyway
⚡️ Tired? Rest. Then show up again
⚡️ It's a slow process but quitting won't speed it up
⚡️ Don't let all the growing pains go to waste: make a win list, take credit, realize how much you learned, and keep going

because YOU DESERVE TO HAVE IT ALL

As a Muslim, a child of immigrants, and a first-generation American, never did I think that the day would come where I would get invited to the white house, let alone to celebrate Eid so proudly with my non muslim friends.

Being Muslim in this country hasn’t always been easy. Especially post 9-11. There was a point in life where I was scared to share my religious background. As I became CEO and a mother of little girls, the story shifted for me because I realized how important representation is: You can’t be - what you cant see.

Today, I’m celebrating Eid inside a room of diverse female founders who opened a space for me to vulnerably share my story and who celebrated with me. I’ll be home tonight to celebrate with my family, and next week ... I will be spending the holiday with The President of the United States @joebiden and Vice President @kamalaharris 

 I’ve received an invitation to continue my celebration inside the White House where it will be celebrated as a multicultural holiday.  That’s what progress looks like and I pray that one day my girls can celebrate this same holiday as an official national holiday at their schools , and with their friends proudly.

I wish my dad could be here to see how times are changing and how proud I am of being Pakistani and Muslim. I see now that it's because of - not in spite of - our immigrant family values that we've been so successful in business and in life. Being Pakistani and American is what makes us unique.

Wishing everyone today celebrating - Eid Mubarak. May this year bring you community, health, prosperity, and abundance.

In tears,

Suneera

“Suneera, what do you do to prepare for a crazy busy week? 🤔”

I get this question a LOT. The answer? Sunday resets. (Especially after a week away from home!!)

When I tell you I can’t afford to NOT zoom out and reset on Sundays! I 100% recommend if you’re a CEO or a working mom. Here’s what I do to ensure a successful week ahead ⤵️

1️⃣ Make sure my pantry is stocked and ready for the week so I don’t have to make ay last-minute grocery store runs that can take time away from my needle movers

2️⃣ I organize my fridge: No reason other than I’m type A and love it 

3️⃣ Backup reset with the girls. You wouldn’t believe the things I find in there 🤢 AND I make sure I go over their homework and congratulate them on their week of hard work at school 

4️⃣ Schedule alignment with @fmadhani. This ensures we’re on the same page for kids’ pickup and drop off schedules and we that we spend enough Q time as a family

5️⃣ Calendar review, of course. I prep for the week ahead & remove meetings that don’t align with my needle movers that week 

6️⃣ Last but not least: I (try to) select my outfits for the week so I don’t waste any time in the morning. 

Did I miss anything? Drop a comment to let me know what YOU do to prepare for the week ahead 👇🏽

This last week @pacecenterforgirls awarded me with their Foundation Builder award and I couldn’t be more honored. 

Pace holds a special place in my heart as the first non profit organization I was ever involved in as the CEO of Stax. 

Sal, my co-founder, and I, have always believed in giving back. So, naturally, when we saw our growth at Stax, we knew we had to find a way to use our success for impact; to show that we cared - as a business but most importantly as important leaders in the community . And that’s how Stax Cares came to be. Our way of making sure that our success meant something for everyone, not just for us. We pledged 1 million dollars of our time , knowledge, and resources to our community . 

Pace was the organization we chose as Stax Cares’ first accomplishment and we couldn’t have chosen a better way to start our impact. Supporting women starts with supporting our youth, and Pace does a beautiful job at providing girls and young women an opportunity for a better future through education, counseling, training, and advocacy. 

Every girl and woman deserves a future to look forward to, and I’m grateful and honored to have had the opportunity to support this cause and be one of this organization’s foundation builders for the last several years. Pace will forever live on with me, even after my time at Stax.

I want to give credit and congratulations to the rest of Pace’s foundation builders for all their hard work as well @kayrawlins46 Rudy Sosa-Febo, Suzanne Worthington, Elise MacCarroll-Wright, amongst others. And a big shoutout to @katievrosa because we couldn’t have built Stax Cares without her. Katie , remember that there is no such thing as a billion dollar idea - only a billion dollar execution - glad we will always continue to execute and finish the job even after it’s done 🤍

I'm all about empowering women and today is all about empowering female entrepreneurs during challenging economic times. Here are five essential tips to help you grow your business successfully during a recession. ⬇️ 

1. The business version of "don't put all your eggs in one basket": Diversify your revenue streams. During a recession, relying solely on one revenue source can be risky. 

2. Your existing customers are your most valuable assets! Make sure you keep them satisfied and consider offering loyalty programs or exclusive deals to encourage them to stay. 

3. Embrace digital marketing. In today's digital age, having a strong online presence is critical. 

4. During a recession, financial management becomes paramount. Educate yourself, keep a close eye on your business's financial health, and create a budget. 

5. Building a strong network of like-minded entrepreneurs and potential collaborators is invaluable. THIS is where I can support you ⬇️ 

Need a close-knit circle of female entrepreneurs to support you during hard times and to celebrate alongside you during good times? Join The CEO School Membership:

When visualizing your highest self, talking about finances, and learning how to dress to attract success come together to make the best first day of the CEO School Retreat. Here’s a recap of the magic that’s happening inside the room 🌟 ⬇️ 

🖤 @innerbeautybybel opened the day with the BEST visualization exercises we’ve seen in a long time. She encouraged us to write words of love and gratefulness to our younger selves while offering compassion for the tools we had back then. It’s all about recognizing that things haven’t gotten easier, we’ve just gotten better and wiser. Afterward, we visualized our future selves and it’s safe to say this energy has us ready to get 👏 shit 👏 done 👏 
🖤 The second workshop was all about marketing. Hosted by @bugaboousa General Manager, @jeanelleteves, we dove deep into our performance marketing roadmap and learned what we should be focusing on, how to segment our marketing, what data we need to set ourselves up for success, and overall just learned from Jeanelle’s experience. Fun fact: Before working at Bugaboo, Jeanelle had a decade-long career at @nike where she launched new product categories including Nike’s first dance & yoga line for plus-size and pregnant women. 
🖤 As if alll of that value wasn’t enough, @chelletaylor30 from @gfgsolutions brought in the magic with The 7-Figure CEO’s Financial Plan workshop. From asset protection and tax planning, to accumulation & diversification and legacy planning, Michelle created a safe space for female founders to talk 👏 about 👏 money 👏 (which is super hard to come by!)
🖤 Last but most definitely not least, @danieli_nieri taught the last workshop of the day. Danieli is a personal and corporate image consultant passionate about dressing women for success. She dove deep into how to awaken our best selves through our personal image and we can’t wait to go home and execute 💅 

Woo! Can you believe this is only ONE day of lessons? Stay tuned to see what tomorrow brings 😉

With the busyness, the chaos, the fact that the way I show up for this community is mostly online, and just life in general, it’s easy for my why to get a bit blurry. Not because my reason for doing it changes -that never wavers- but because I lose the magnitude of the impact that we’re having as a company and I start to wonder if my efforts are enough. 

That’s why events like this one fill my cup and leave my heart feeling so full. Because seeing amazing women go from being unsure if they’re good enough to be in the room, to being certain that that same room was their missing piece all along and that they’re not only good enough to be in it, but that it’s the place where they truly belong, is priceless. 

I’m grateful and honored that I have the opportunity to facilitate safe spaces like this one for CEOs to reconnect with their why, gain clarity, and leave feeling fired up to unlock a new level of success. Because if you can’t see it, you can’t be it, and being in a room full of women who ARE IT, suddenly changes the game. 

To the women who joined us this week, thank you for trusting me to be part of your journey and, with it, reconnecting me with my why. I. Can’t wait to see the lengths you’ll go to. 

To the women who couldn’t join us, let this be your nudge to take the leap and join us in December. You won’t regret it. 

With love,
Sunny

This is how the game changed for me 🙌🏽Instead of stressing myself out with hitting huge numbers at the end of the year (which leaves way too many variables to chance and way too many gaps where balls can be dropped) I started planning every single quarter. And I don't mean just a big picture plan: I mean an actionable, step-by-step plan that I stick with daily like my bible. Hands down the reason why I started hitting all my revenue goals, when I finally felt like I had freedom of time, and when I no longer felt burned out, was when I started crafting and perfecting my quarterly plans ✍🏼

That’s why, every quarter, I host a quarterly planning session for all the female founders inside my membership 🌟

That “little business” will build generational wealth, thank you very much. 

Ever get tired of having to constantly prove yourself to others when you know d*mn well that you’re building something special? 

Yeah, me too! 

I got you, though: Here are four ways to ensure you go all out in 2024 so you can show the world (and, most importantly, YOU) what you’re capable of. 

1️⃣ Take risks.

Many people are afraid to take risks because they don’t want to fail or let people down. Growing up, women usually aren’t encouraged to move outside their comfort zones. As a society, we praise boys for trying new things and getting their hands on messy things but ask girls not to get dirty and to sit on the sidelines.

Make sure you break the pattern and take 👏🏽 that 👏🏽 risk 👏🏽

2️⃣ Aim for progress, not perfection. 

You may have seen the report floating around that found men will apply for a job if they feel they’re 60% qualified, but women won’t unless they feel 100% prepared or “perfect” for the job. 

Though done is better than perfect, it seems many women didn’t get the memo. Well, you’re getting it now: Take action, however imperfect, to make progress.

3️⃣ Have confidence in your competence. 

It’s possible to be confident but still lack confidence in your abilities. For example, women are notorious for engaging in self-sabotaging talk. 
On the other hand, men seem to take compliments, even if they aren’t warranted. 

Lean into your abilities and push yourself to get out of your comfort zone. 

4️⃣ Dream big. 

In my experience coaching thousands of women, most define business success as hitting six figures and having some flexibility for their families.

When I first started, I never knew I could build a billion-dollar business and I hadn’t seen any women doing it. But as I focused on growing and scaling my business, I found other female founders doing the same.

Make sure you dream big because when female founders know what’s possible, it raises the bar for everyone. 🌟

No excuses. Just an unbreakable spirit and a fire drive.

LET’S GO! 💥

You NEED to get in the right rooms to scale your business. Here’s why ⬇️ 

Entrepreneurship often feels like 

👉🏽 You’re sacrificing all the balance in your life yet still find yourself not being able to scale your business

👉🏽 You’re spending your days solving everyone else’s problems instead of zooming out and seeing the bigger picture

👉🏽 No one around you gets it so you can’t get the guidance you so desperately need

👉🏽 Everyone looks to YOU for answers but, sometimes, you don’t have them and you wish you had someone that could mentor you through those blockers 

If you can relate to most, if not all of those ⬆️, you’re on the right track: It means you built a business from the ground up and scaled it past your abilities and expertise. 

And... That’s OK! In fact. it’s a good sign. You’re NOT supposed to have all the answers. 

Here’s what you ARE supposed to do, though: 

Find a circle of women who just... get it. Women who are where you want to be and who are going even further and want YOU to come along with them. More experienced women, who can challenge you, and who can show you what’s possible.

Showing my girls today that falling is part of the cycle, what makes us stronger is the rise - and this rise feels WAY more metaphoric in my journey this year through it all .

Instead of just focusing on resolutions to add, how about things to let go of . This has been my list for a few years now , it’s not easy but it’s time to let it gooo ❄️ 

7 Things to quit in 2024 

- people pleasing 
- overthinking 
- self shaming 
-resentment towards family members 
-living in the past 
- an ego
-apologizing for putting yourself first 

Who’s with me ? Which one  is your toxic trait holding you back ? 👇🏽

Be brave enough to build the life you want and courageous enough to *let it all go* when it doesn’t align anymore. ✨

Never thought I would actually achieve building the life I always dreamt of - and never thought when I actually had it all …  i would be willing to let it all go . 

2023 was a year of healing and transition , a lot of hard questions on fulfillment and answers unknown but the willingness to know I’m  made for more than the the material success I amassed . 

The funny thing about life is you chase and you chase , but what happens when you actually achieve it ? The thrill of life is *the journey* , and when you reach whatever you think is the pinnacle - it leaves you yearning for other fulfillment - so you decide to re align - to let go - to start over - and I’m beyond proud of my journey this year in truly shedding and re inventing who i want to be . 

The Suneera you knew I’m so proud of too - but I’m shedding all her labels . Re inventing again in this next decade of chasing life on my terms and doing it all over again because *spoiler alert*  having it *all* is not what it’s all about - it’s about doing life on your *terms* . And I’m now able to say .. this time i get to do it with full confidence in who i am *AND* who i want to be . 🙏🏽

2023 was also a realization year that not all humans are the humans you wish them to be - even if you go in with 100% of heart ( #freepalestine , #stax #life ) - it leaves you tainted but you must protect that human heart of yours because the world needs more of you now* than ever . 

Reminder : Your energy is a privilege , your heart is pure , your life is the company you keep and the support you need when no one’s watching - be willing to let go of your past to make way for your future - even if your past was exactly where you thought you wanted to be — 

You are allowed to *re-invent it all* and *thats* the beauty of growth and being human . 

Cheers to 2024 a new year , an even better , more confident, more protected , more experienced — but still with *all my heart* me ✔️

Suneera
